---
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
import "../styles/landing.css";
---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>About — EdgeCMS</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Why EdgeCMS exists: your idea, on your own domain, running free — no budget required to start."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href="/assets/logo.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <SiteHeader active="about" />

    <section class="ec-section">
      <div class="ec-wrap" style="max-width:720px;padding:88px 40px 60px">
        <img src="/assets/logo.svg" alt="The EdgeCMS edge mark" width="56" height="56" style="display:block;margin-bottom:32px" />
        <p class="ec-mono" style="font-size:28px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-0.02em;color:var(--text-1);line-height:1.3;margin:0 0 40px">
          You don't need a big budget — just a big enough blade.
        </p>

        <p style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:var(--text-2)">
          EdgeCMS began with a question heard again and again from app builders in the Philippines:
          <em>"where can I put this online for free?"</em> Too many good ideas never go live because
          hosting costs money someone doesn't have yet — not because the idea, or the builder, wasn't
          good enough.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:var(--text-2)">
          So the whole product promise is one thing: your idea, on your own domain, running free — no
          budget required to start. <code>edgecms login → init → deploy</code> provisions Workers, D1,
          R2, and KV on your own Cloudflare account, entirely on its permanent free tier. You own the
          domain. You own the data. There's no seat to pay for.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:var(--text-2)">
          We kept it to a guided setup instead of a control panel full of choices, because the point
          isn't to learn a new tool — it's to get your work in front of people today.
        </p>

        <h2 class="ec-h2" style="font-size:22px;margin:48px 0 16px">What we won't do</h2>
        <ul style="font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.8;color:var(--text-2);padding-left:1.2em;margin:0">
          <li>No seat pricing, ever — the CMS itself doesn't charge you anything.</li>
          <li>
            The only dependency is Cloudflare, said plainly, not hidden — you're running on their free
            tier, and the one optional paid feature (semantic search, via Vectorize) is flagged before
            you turn it on.
          </li>
          <li>No fake "free forever*" — every claim on this site is true of the current release.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="ec-h2" style="font-size:22px;margin:48px 0 16px">Open source</h2>
        <p style="font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:var(--text-2)">
          EdgeCMS is open source — read the code, file an issue, or send a pull request on
          <a href="https://github.com/periabyte/edge-cms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
        </p>

        <div class="ec-command" style="max-width:420px;margin-top:40px">
          <div class="ec-command-row">
            <span class="ec-command-code"><span class="ec-prompt">$</span>npx edgecms init</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <SiteFooter />
  </body>
</html>
